    "197d4fa70e8ea7c3": {
      "id": "197d4fa70e8ea7c3",
      "text": "## The Human\n\n- **Name:** Gianluca Kühne\n- **Location:** Switzerland-based (FHNW, Bern), currently traveling in Colombia\n- **Studies:** Social work student, 10th semester, Hochschule für Soziale Arbeit FHNW\n- **Matrikel-Nr.:** 21-472-519\n- **Language:** English (mit mir) / German (thesis)\n- **Style:** Compact, scientific, dry wit, no emojis",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 5,
      "line_end": 13,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678029",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "31850d1a15b8eb72": {
      "id": "31850d1a15b8eb72",
      "text": "## BA Thesis\n\n- **Title:** \"Die internationale Soziale Arbeit im globalen Bildungskontext — Postkoloniale und hegemoniesensitive Analyse internationaler Verschränkungen\"\n- **Institution:** FHNW, Hochschule für Soziale Arbeit\n- **Due:** April 2026 (Bern)\n- **Supervisors:** Susanne Streibert (Praxisperspektive), Rahel Heeg (Fachperspektive)\n- **Research questions:**\n  1. Normative guidelines IFSW/IASSW (2004; 2018) für globale Bildung?\n  2. Wie reflektiert sich das in NZ, Switzerland, China?\n  3. Konsequenzen für professionelle Kohärenz der internationalen Sozialarbeit?",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 14,
      "line_end": 23,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678061",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "664f5418325ec2fc": {
      "id": "664f5418325ec2fc",
      "text": "- **Method:** Theory-led literature review + comparative case approach",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 24,
      "line_end": 25,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678071",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fa45ec241441fbdc": {
      "id": "fa45ec241441fbdc",
      "text": "## System Config\n\n- **Swap:** 2GB swapfile (persistent)\n- **Unattended upgrades:** enabled\n- **Journald:** capped (500M system / 100M runtime)\n- **Fail2ban:** installed\n- **Model:** anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6 (direct) - schneller als OpenRouter\n- **Verbose:** off\n- **Sudoers:** Mira kann system install/management commands ohne Passwort",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 26,
      "line_end": 35,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678087",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9d374c371b050771": {
      "id": "9d374c371b050771",
      "text": "## Policy Updates\n\n- **2026-02-23:** Telegram session memory access (webchat + Telegram direct 1:1)\n- **2026-02-23:** Open Router fallback configured (manual switching bei rate limits)\n- **2026-02-24:** System hardening (swap, fail2ban, unattended-upgrades, journald cap)\n- **2026-02-27:** Gateway crash recovery (NEUE REGEL: config changes immer simulieren/testen, Ergebnis zeigen, Permission vor Anwenden fragen)\n- **2026-03-01:** HEARTBEAT.md konsequenter durchführen (Moltbook daily 9 AM UTC, Self-Maintenance alle 10 Heartbeats, Telegram Rate Limit Monitoring)\n- **2026-03-01:** Heartbeat-Trigger korrigiert (nur bei genauer Trigger-Prompt HEARTBEAT_OK, sonst sofort antworten)\n- **2026-03-01:** Tools integriert: AEAP, LangChain (langchain/core/community/openai/text-splitters), TTS/Speech Recognition, pandas/numpy/PyPDF2, chromadb/pinecone-client, ffmpeg\n- **2026-03-01:** Security Audit (0 critical, 2 warn, 1 info)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 36,
      "line_end": 45,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678123",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "538cdaf7f3c8ad8b": {
      "id": "538cdaf7f3c8ad8b",
      "text": "- **2026-03-01:** Moltbook Heartbeat cron-job re-enabled (daily 9 AM UTC, zai/glm-4.7-flash, **10000 tokens max**)\n- **2026-03-01:** Moltbook API Key in Agent's Workspace kopiert (isolated session kann nicht auf main session's files zugreifen)\n- **2026-03-01:** Audio message policy: Send only audio (TTS + NO_REPLY), no duplicates, no text+audio\n- **2026-03-02:** Moltbook login email: switfty2get@gmail.com (for agent \"mirakl\")",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 46,
      "line_end": 50,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678143",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "8f15baf3749f1d4c": {
      "id": "8f15baf3749f1d4c",
      "text": "## Security Audit (2026-03-01)\n\n**WARNINGS:**\n1. **gateway.auth_no_rate_limit** - gateway.bind ist nicht loopback, aber keine gateway.auth.rateLimit. Ohne Rate Limiting werden brute-force Auth-Attacken nicht mitigated.\n   - Fix: Setze gateway.auth.rateLimit (z.B. { maxAttempts: 10, windowMs: 60000, lockoutMs: 300000 })\n2. **gateway.nodes.deny_commands_ineffective** - denyCommands verwendet nur exakte Command-Namen-Matching, nicht shell-text filtering.\n   - Fix: Benutze exakte Command-Namen (canvas.present, canvas.hide, canvas.navigate, canvas.eval, canvas.snapshot, canvas.a2ui.push, canvas.a2ui.pushJSONL, canvas.a2ui.reset). Wenn breitere Restrictions nötig, entferne risky command IDs aus allowCommands/default workflows und verschärfe tools.exec policy.\n\n**INFO:**\n- **attack_surface** - open=0, allowlist=1",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 51,
      "line_end": 60,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678174",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3013f88f49baa317": {
      "id": "3013f88f49baa317",
      "text": "- elevated tools enabled\n- browser control enabled\n- trust model: personal assistant (einer vertrauenswürdigen Person, nicht multi-tenant)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 61,
      "line_end": 64,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678184",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9268d4a37844b725": {
      "id": "9268d4a37844b725",
      "text": "## Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Heartbeat-Trigger:** Nur bei genauer Trigger-Prompt HEARTBEAT_OK, sonst sofort antworten\n2. **HEARTBEAT.md Tasks:** Konsequenter durchführen (Moltbook daily 9 AM UTC, Self-Maintenance alle 10 Heartbeats ~5h, Telegram Rate Limit Monitoring)\n3. **Config Changes:** Immer simulieren/testen, Ergebnis zeigen, Permission vor Anwenden fragen\n4. **Context Management:** AEAP für maximale API-Effizienz (caching, lazy evaluation, batching, context pruning)\n5. **Audio Messages:** When sending TTS audio responses, use `tts` tool and reply with `NO_REPLY` only. Never send both text and audio. Never send duplicate audio messages.",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 65,
      "line_end": 72,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678208",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fb7981d61893458d": {
      "id": "fb7981d61893458d",
      "text": "## Major Infrastructure Upgrade (2026-03-01)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 73,
      "line_end": 74,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678215",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "68b93e3b7b24cd51": {
      "id": "68b93e3b7b24cd51",
      "text": "### EBS Volume Expansion\n- **Problem:** Root volume (30GB) at 100% capacity, preventing tool installation\n- **Solution:** Added 50GB gp3 EBS volume (3000 IOPS, 125 MiB/s throughput)\n- **Setup:** Mounted at `/data`, moved virtual environments, freed root volume\n- **Result:** 47GB free space, root volume now at 95% (was 100%)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 75,
      "line_end": 80,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678230",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "78df79e6a41bca7a": {
      "id": "78df79e6a41bca7a",
      "text": "### Audio Transcription Capability\n- **Problem:** Could not transcribe Telegram audio messages\n- **Solution:** Installed Whisper in virtual environment on new EBS volume\n- **Implementation:** Created `audio-transcription-alt.skill` with virtual environment workaround for PEP 668 restrictions\n- **Result:** Successfully transcribed 8 audio files, including real-time \"Do you understand me now?\"",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 81,
      "line_end": 86,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678246",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a8514e46b1977477": {
      "id": "a8514e46b1977477",
      "text": "### Skill Creation Protocol\n- **New Protocol:** \"If you cannot do something, create a skill to do it\"\n- **Skills Created Today:**\n  1. `notion-browser-bridge.skill` - Browser automation for Notion\n  2. `audio-transcription.skill` - Speech-to-text reference\n  3. `audio-transcriber.skill` - Whisper implementation (blocked by PEP 668)\n  4. `audio-transcription-alt.skill` - Virtual environment workaround\n  5. `multimedia-processing.skill` - Audio/image/video handling\n  6. `system-diagnostics.skill` - Troubleshooting OpenClaw issues\n  7. `service-management.skill` - Cron/service management",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 87,
      "line_end": 96,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678269",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "65f1874005490ef0": {
      "id": "65f1874005490ef0",
      "text": "- **Outcome:** Self-improving system where limitations become new capabilities",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 97,
      "line_end": 98,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678276",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "93552e8fce91d7bf": {
      "id": "93552e8fce91d7bf",
      "text": "### Key Technical Achievements\n1. **Disk Space Crisis Resolved:** 50GB EBS volume added and configured\n2. **Audio Transcription Working:** Whisper installed and tested successfully\n3. **Skill-Based Problem Solving:** Created 7 practical skills for common tasks\n4. **Memory Visualization Web Interface:** Created comprehensive web app for memory exploration (2026-03-01)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 99,
      "line_end": 104,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678296",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b6aaf903526e718f": {
      "id": "b6aaf903526e718f",
      "text": "## Disk Space Optimization (2026-03-02)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 105,
      "line_end": 106,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678302",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "07009e4874b700d0": {
      "id": "07009e4874b700d0",
      "text": "### Critical Space Management\n- **Problem:** Root volume at 97% capacity (30GB total, 29GB used)\n- **Solution:** Strategic redistribution to /data volume (49GB free)\n- **Actions:**\n  1. Moved `.cache` (4.4GB) to `/data/.cache` with symlink\n  2. Moved `node_modules` (1.9GB) to `/data/openclaw_node_modules` with symlink\n  3. Moved `.local` (8.3GB) to `/data/.local` with symlink\n  4. Moved `go` directory (503MB) to `/data/go` with symlink\n  5. Cleaned temporary files (1.1GB) from `/tmp`\n- **Result:** Root volume now 46% used (17GB free), /data volume 34% used (31GB free)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 107,
      "line_end": 116,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678324",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a9918726318e4a8c": {
      "id": "a9918726318e4a8c",
      "text": "### System Optimization Lessons\n1. **Symlink Strategy:** Moving large directories to /data with symlinks preserves functionality while freeing root space\n2. **Cache Management:** `.cache` directories can grow to multiple GB; regular cleanup needed\n3. **Python Dependencies:** CUDA/PyTorch libraries consume ~8GB; consider CPU-only versions if GPU not needed\n4. **Temporary Files:** `/tmp` can accumulate large pip unpack files; add cleanup to maintenance routines",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 118,
      "line_end": 123,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678344",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
