    "debdb6690093105e": {
      "id": "debdb6690093105e",
      "text": "## Tool Integration Challenges (2026-03-02)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 352,
      "line_end": 353,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678863",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ae7c43b3b42c99d2": {
      "id": "ae7c43b3b42c99d2",
      "text": "### Claude Code Interaction Limitations\n- **Problem:** Claude CLI requires true interactive terminal, not pipes or simulated keyboard input\n- **Challenge:** OpenClaw's exec/process tools have limitations with PTY interaction\n- **Discovery:** Claude CLI designed for interactive terminal sessions, not programmatic stdin\n- **Working method:** Direct terminal access via SSH or Termius, then run `claude`\n- **Status:** Claude Code installed and works (responds to `--print` when communication succeeds)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 354,
      "line_end": 360,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678882",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6bc685cfa927d6a4": {
      "id": "6bc685cfa927d6a4",
      "text": "### Termius Multiplayer Link Processing\n- **Link format:** `https://termius.com/terminal-multiplayer#peerId=...&terminalTitle=...&connectionId=...&version=...&pwd=...`\n- **Created skill:** `external-terminal-access` with link parser (`process_link.py`)\n- **Capability:** Parse Termius links, extract connection details, provide access instructions\n- **Limitation:** Cannot join Termius sessions programmatically without Termius CLI/API\n- **Alternative:** SSH direct access: `ssh ubuntu@172.31.14.61`",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 361,
      "line_end": 367,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678901",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d1c3cee46104fcdb": {
      "id": "d1c3cee46104fcdb",
      "text": "### CLI API Documentation Tool\n- **Created:** `print_cli_api.py` - comprehensive CLI API reference\n- **Covers:** Claude, OpenClaw, MCPorter, SSH, cURL, Git, Termius\n- **Usage:** `python3 print_cli_api.py [tool|all]`\n- **Purpose:** Quick reference for all available command-line interfaces",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 368,
      "line_end": 373,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678915",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1b7dd643766ef82c": {
      "id": "1b7dd643766ef82c",
      "text": "### External Terminal Access Skill\n- **Skill:** `external-terminal-access` (created March 2, 2026)\n- **Components:**\n  1. SKILL.md with comprehensive access methods\n  2. `process_link.py` for Termius link parsing\n  3. Root skill file for quick reference\n- **Git commit:** `a2b0f55` - \"Create external terminal access skill\"",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 374,
      "line_end": 381,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678930",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f103be9fc2be32c0": {
      "id": "f103be9fc2be32c0",
      "text": "### Communication Protocol Refinement\n- **Issue:** Repeated use of pipes despite instruction to use keyboard simulation\n- **Root cause:** Tool limitations and habitual patterns\n- **Learning:** Acknowledge tool limitations rather than attempting workarounds that violate instructions\n- **Rule:** When a tool cannot fulfill a request properly, state the limitation clearly",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 382,
      "line_end": 387,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678945",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3da10f816c6530af": {
      "id": "3da10f816c6530af",
      "text": "### System Status\n- **Background tasks:** All closed as requested\n- **Gateway:** Running on port 18789\n- **Disk space:** Root 96% full, /data 5% used\n- **Models:** DeepSeek Reasoner (current), Claude Sonnet 4-6 available, Opus not configured\n- **Heartbeat:** All tasks current, Moltbook scheduled for 9 AM UTC",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 388,
      "line_end": 394,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.678960",
      "embedding_shape": [
