    "711837a3a1e96905": {
      "id": "711837a3a1e96905",
      "text": "## Model Compatibility (2026-03-02)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 466,
      "line_end": 467,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679142",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "91f04fbe4c3f1ff8": {
      "id": "91f04fbe4c3f1ff8",
      "text": "### DeepSeek API Issue\n- **Problem:** \"400 Missing reasoning_content field in the assistant message at message index 565\"\n- **Cause:** DeepSeek thinking mode requires specific API format that OpenClaw may not support\n- **Solution:** Switched to Claude Sonnet 4-6 for reliable operation\n- **Learning:** Different model providers have different API requirements; need compatibility testing",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 468,
      "line_end": 473,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679157",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e6cef17224742197": {
      "id": "e6cef17224742197",
      "text": "### Current Model Configuration\n- **Primary:** Claude Sonnet 4-6 (direct) - stable, reliable\n- **Fallback:** DeepSeek Reasoner - use with caution due to API compatibility issues\n- **Available:** Open Router Claude Sonnet 4-6 (for Telegram rate limit fallback)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 474,
      "line_end": 478,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679169",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "4cde3adcfe585a7b": {
      "id": "4cde3adcfe585a7b",
      "text": "## Multi-Model Orchestrator Implementation (2026-03-02)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 479,
      "line_end": 480,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679175",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7c8f9c9e33904b54": {
      "id": "7c8f9c9e33904b54",
      "text": "### Problem Solved\n- **Complex task completion:** No single AI model excels at all types of tasks\n- **Solution:** Coordinate multiple specialized models to work together\n- **Inspiration:** Perplexity Computer's approach to multi-model task completion",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 481,
      "line_end": 485,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679187",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fa56107473d4426c": {
      "id": "fa56107473d4426c",
      "text": "### Architecture\n1. **Task Analysis & Decomposition**\n   - Analyzes task complexity (simple, moderate, complex, extreme)\n   - Breaks complex tasks into subtasks based on patterns\n   - Identifies required capabilities for each subtask\n\n2. **Model Registry & Selection**\n   - **Model profiles:** Track capabilities and strength scores\n   - **Capability matching:** REASONING, CREATIVITY, CODING, RESEARCH, ANALYSIS, WRITING, PLANNING, REVIEW, SPECIALIST\n   - **Strength scoring:** Models rated 0.0-1.0 for each capability",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 486,
      "line_end": 495,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679208",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "79e0eb437e7208b9": {
      "id": "79e0eb437e7208b9",
      "text": "- **Optimal selection:** Choose best model for each subtask\n\n3. **Workflow Coordination**\n   - **Sequential:** Models run one after another (for dependent tasks)\n   - **Parallel:** Independent subtasks executed simultaneously\n   - **Hierarchical:** Master model delegates to specialists\n   - **Ensemble:** Multiple models vote/combine outputs\n\n4. **Result Integration**\n   - Combines outputs from multiple models",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 496,
      "line_end": 505,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679226",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "43a868c83dbbb579": {
      "id": "43a868c83dbbb579",
      "text": "- Calculates overall confidence score\n   - Provides execution metadata and model usage tracking",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 506,
      "line_end": 508,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679234",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3dcec60bf4a518cf": {
      "id": "3dcec60bf4a518cf",
      "text": "### Implementation Details\n- **Skill:** `multi-model-orchestrator` (created March 2, 2026)\n- **Core classes:** `MultiModelOrchestrator`, `ModelProfile`, `Subtask`, `TaskDecomposition`, `OrchestrationResult`\n- **Model registry:** Pre-configured with claude-sonnet, gpt-4, gemini-pro, llama-code profiles\n- **Workflow patterns:** Research reports, software development, comparative analysis",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 509,
      "line_end": 514,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679250",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "517e8ae2db69a600": {
      "id": "517e8ae2db69a600",
      "text": "### Example Use Cases\n1. **Research Report:** Research → Outline → Write → Review (sequential)\n2. **Software Development:** Requirements → Design → Implement → Test (sequential)\n3. **Comparative Analysis:** Research A + Research B → Analyze → Synthesize (parallel + sequential)\n4. **Complex Analysis:** Multiple specialists work on different aspects simultaneously",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 515,
      "line_end": 520,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679267",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "70f443357e9f73cf": {
      "id": "70f443357e9f73cf",
      "text": "### Integration Points\n- **Perplexity-Inspired Skill:** Enhanced query analysis for task decomposition\n- **Async Agent Pattern:** Handles long-running multi-model workflows\n- **Heartbeat System:** Can schedule complex multi-model tasks\n- **Memory System:** Tracks orchestration history and model performance",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 521,
      "line_end": 526,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679281",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "14e446142dbc13eb": {
      "id": "14e446142dbc13eb",
      "text": "### Key Features\n- **Automatic task decomposition:** Pattern-based subtask identification\n- **Intelligent model selection:** Capability matching with strength scoring\n- **Flexible workflows:** Sequential, parallel, hierarchical, ensemble\n- **Mock execution:** Simulation mode for testing without API calls\n- **History tracking:** Records all orchestration attempts and results",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 527,
      "line_end": 533,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679297",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fe0bb7273079668d": {
      "id": "fe0bb7273079668d",
      "text": "### Future Enhancements\n1. **Real model integration:** Connect to actual AI model APIs\n2. **Learning system:** Improve model selection based on past performance\n3. **Cost optimization:** Balance quality vs. cost across different models\n4. **Quality validation:** Cross-checking between model outputs\n5. **Dynamic workflow:** Adaptive workflow selection based on task characteristics",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 534,
      "line_end": 540,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679313",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "380c234c476fb391": {
      "id": "380c234c476fb391",
      "text": "### Git Commit\n- **Commit:** `2c59d06` - \"Add multi-model orchestrator skill\"\n- **Files:** SKILL.md, multi_model_orchestrator.py, examples/basic_usage.py\n- **Status:** Implemented, tested, committed to GitHub",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 541,
      "line_end": 545,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679323",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "82edbcce847f3564": {
      "id": "82edbcce847f3564",
      "text": "## Entrosana.com Dashboard Connection Setup (2026-03-02)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 546,
      "line_end": 547,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679329",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "18ecb35600bffffa": {
      "id": "18ecb35600bffffa",
      "text": "### **Architecture:**\n1. **OpenClaw Gateway**: Port 18789 (local)\n2. **NGINX Reverse Proxy**: Port 443 (HTTPS) → Port 18789\n3. **DNS**: entrosana.com → 18.225.98.79 (EC2 public IP)\n4. **SSL**: Let's Encrypt certificate via Certbot",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 548,
      "line_end": 553,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679343",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fe769d002691e32d": {
      "id": "fe769d002691e32d",
      "text": "### **Firewall Layers (All Must Allow):**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 554,
      "line_end": 555,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679349",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ea0e4be1176ab9f8": {
      "id": "ea0e4be1176ab9f8",
      "text": "#### **1. AWS Security Group (EC2 Level)**\n- **Port 443**: Allow 0.0.0.0/0 (HTTPS)\n- **Port 18789**: Allow specific IPs or 0.0.0.0/0\n- **Check**: EC2 → Security Groups → Inbound Rules",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 556,
      "line_end": 560,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679361",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d4e4aad66a08c703": {
      "id": "d4e4aad66a08c703",
      "text": "#### **2. AWS Network ACL (Subnet Level - STATEFUL)**\n- **INBOUND**: Must allow port 443 AND destination port (18789 after proxy)\n- **OUTBOUND**: Must allow ephemeral ports (1024-65535) for responses\n- **Common Issue**: Rule 101 too restrictive (only port 443, blocks 18789)\n- **Fix**: Change to \"All Traffic\" or add rule for port 18789\n- **Check**: VPC → Network ACLs → Associated with subnet",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 561,
      "line_end": 567,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679380",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "765c9fc0b59b85f9": {
      "id": "765c9fc0b59b85f9",
      "text": "#### **3. Instance Firewall (UFW)**\n- **Port 443**: `sudo ufw allow 443/tcp`\n- **Port 18789**: `sudo ufw allow 18789/tcp`\n- **Check**: `sudo ufw status verbose`\n- **Default**: deny (incoming) - must explicitly allow ports",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 568,
      "line_end": 573,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679408",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "46ba8fd023193c01": {
      "id": "46ba8fd023193c01",
      "text": "### **NGINX Configuration:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 574,
      "line_end": 599,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679417",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6ed4cedd56a63617": {
      "id": "6ed4cedd56a63617",
      "text": "### **Diagnostic Commands:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 600,
      "line_end": 601,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679422",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9a8e2ed34b0c9a31": {
      "id": "9a8e2ed34b0c9a31",
      "text": "#### **Check Connectivity:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 602,
      "line_end": 619,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679429",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "70dc473ad01ebc57": {
      "id": "70dc473ad01ebc57",
      "text": "#### **Check AWS Configuration:**\n- **Security Group**: Port 443 allows 0.0.0.0/0\n- **NACL**: Both inbound AND outbound allow traffic\n- **Route Table**: 0.0.0.0/0 → Internet Gateway",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 620,
      "line_end": 624,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679440",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1e0f23162864baa9": {
      "id": "1e0f23162864baa9",
      "text": "### **Common Error Patterns:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 625,
      "line_end": 626,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679446",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "462565976f9678d6": {
      "id": "462565976f9678d6",
      "text": "#### **\"disconnected (1006): no reason\"**\n- WebSocket connection failing\n- Check NGINX WebSocket headers (`Upgrade`, `Connection`)\n- Check gateway WebSocket support",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 627,
      "line_end": 631,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679455",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "dd94588c6a9de477": {
      "id": "dd94588c6a9de477",
      "text": "#### **\"net::ERR_CONNECTION_TIMED_OUT\"**\n- Firewall blocking at some layer\n- Check all 3 firewalls: Security Group, NACL, UFW\n- NACL outbound ephemeral ports often missed",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 632,
      "line_end": 636,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679465",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f0864bb9e79824da": {
      "id": "f0864bb9e79824da",
      "text": "#### **No errors but no connection**\n- NACL inbound too restrictive (only port 443, blocks proxied port 18789)\n- UFW missing port 443 rule",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 637,
      "line_end": 640,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679474",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "877caa6a2dc6130c": {
      "id": "877caa6a2dc6130c",
      "text": "### **Quick Fix Checklist:**\n1. ✅ **Security Group**: Port 443 allows 0.0.0.0/0\n2. ✅ **NACL Inbound**: Allows destination port (18789 after proxy)\n3. ✅ **NACL Outbound**: Allows ephemeral ports (1024-65535)\n4. ✅ **UFW**: `sudo ufw allow 443/tcp`\n5. ✅ **NGINX**: Running and configured\n6. ✅ **Gateway**: Running on port 18789",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 641,
      "line_end": 648,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-03T00:07:26.679490",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2d9e3fb88ee34c1f": {
      "id": "2d9e3fb88ee34c1f",
